Sample gearbox oil immediately after
turbine stop and before change of inline
and offline filters. (Go to menu 30,
select test switch 9, go to menu 25,
scroll to I/O 2 bit 3)
When sampling gear oil for analysis, it
is very important to do this under as
clean conditions as possible. An oil
sample does not require much external
contamination to distort the test result
significantly.
Follow the oil sampling procedure in the
service manual carefully.

subOperations.description:

leaks in the hydraulics system in the
nacelle (filters and fittings) paying
particular attention to the below areas
of concerns. If leakages found, check
condition of o-rings and torque settings
(when depressurised according to site
LOTO).
Valve 41 (If applicable)
Valve 25
Return filter o-ring
Pressure pipe, Pump to block
